                     ws_item, by = c("definition", "category"))

# mitem <- read_csv("match_kr_wg_ws.csv") %>% rename(item_id_wg = `WG(item_id)`, item_id_ws = `WS(item_id)`) %>% mutate(item_id_ws = gsub("-", "_",item_id_ws)) %>% filter(!is.na(item_id_ws))

full_kor_ws_sub <- full_kor_ws %>% filter(item_id %in% common$item_id.y)

Run glmrob on WG data

inv_logit <- function(x) 1/(exp(-x) + 1)
ages <- tibble(age = 8:36)
# glmrob function
glmrob <- function(x){
  robustbase::glmrob(cbind(num_true, num_false) ~ age, 
                   data = x,
                   family = "binomial") %>%
  stats::predict(ages) %>% 
  inv_logit()
}

full_kor_wg_sub %>% 
  dplyr::mutate(produces = !is.na(value) & value == 
                  "produces", 
                understands = !is.na(value) & 
                  (value == "understands" | value == "produces")) %>% 
  dplyr::select(age, num_item_id,  category, definition, produces, understands) %>% 
  tidyr::gather("measure_name", "value", produces, understands) -> item_data_wg

Comprehension

# process measures
item_data_wg %>% 
  dplyr::filter(measure_name == "understands") %>% 
  dplyr::group_by(age, num_item_id,  category, definition) %>% 
  dplyr::summarise(num_true = sum(value), 
                   num_false = dplyr::n() -  num_true) -> 
  item_data_wg_comp
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'age', 'num_item_id', 'category'. You can
## override using the `.groups` argument.
# nest and run glmrob
item_data_wg_comp %>% 
  group_by(num_item_id,  category, definition) %>% 
  nest()  %>%
  mutate(model = map(data, function(x)glmrob(x))) %>% ungroup() -> wg_comp

# tidy data
wg_comp %>% unnest_wider(model) %>% select(-num_item_id) %>%
  rename(category = category,
         definition = definition,
         data = data,
        `8`= `1`, `9`= `2`, `10`= `3`, `11`= `4`, `12`= `5`, `13`= `6`, `14`= `7`, `15`= `8`, `16`= `9`, `17`= `10`, `18`= `11`, `19`= `12`, `20`= `13`, `21`= `14`, `22`= `15`, `23`= `16`, `24`= `17`, `25`= `18`, `26`= `19`, `27`= `20`, `28`= `21`, `29`= `22`, `30`= `23`, `31`= `24`, `32`= `25`, `33`= `26`, `34`= `27`, `35`= `28`, `36`= `29`
) -> tidy_wg_comp

Plot comparisons

Combine data

combine <- rbind(tidy_wg_comp %>% mutate(dataset = "wg", measure = "comp"),
                 tidy_ws_comp %>% mutate(dataset = "ws", measure = "comp"),
                 tidy_wgws_comp %>% mutate(dataset = "wgws", measure = "comp"),
                 tidy_wg_prod %>% mutate(dataset = "wg", measure = "prod"),
                 tidy_ws_prod %>% mutate(dataset = "ws", measure = "prod"),
                 tidy_wgws_prod %>% mutate(dataset = "wgws", measure = "prod")) %>%
  pivot_longer(paste(c(8:36)), names_to = "age", values_to = "pred") %>% 
  mutate(age = as.numeric(age))

Randomly inspect item

Run 1

# randomly inspect item
random_item <- sample(unique(combine$definition), 6)

ggplot(combine %>% filter(definition %in% random_item), aes(y = pred, x = age, col = dataset)) + xlab("Age") + ylab("Predicted Proportion (%)") + geom_jitter() +
  facet_wrap(paste(definition,sep = "_")~measure, ncol = 2)+ggtitle("run #1")
